ëíŸ@2bfceca3d482e5e16bbac71c47abfaa1c4676c861f2eacf1c3d91862d16ba3e0⁄îTitle: This week in Nu #53
Path: This week in Nu #53
Content:
We celebrated our one year of Nu being public with a 
[link: http://www.nushell.sh/blog/2020/08/23/year_of_nushell.html] blog post
amitdev added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2405] configuration to disable hinting in the line editor
andrasio improved the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2441] span logic for pipelines
, cleaned up the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2433] plugin implementation
, cleaned up 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2425] ``autoview``
 and 
``table``
 configuration
, made 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2423] ``insert``
 and 
``update``
 more flexible
, simplified 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2404] command span info
arnaldo2792 improved the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/126] RHEL-based installation instructions
bailey-layzer made 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2418] type inference in 
``alias``
 optional
coolshaurya updated 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2390] ``version``
 with git hash
dmeijboom fixed an 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2437] out of bounds error in 
``headers``
fdncred added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2430] reverse find to 
``index-of``
, added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2429] sample plugin in PowerShell
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2428] ``path dirname``
 and 
``path filestem``
gorogoroumaru made 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2431] ``cd``
 command complete only directories
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2383] ``date``
 subcommands
jonathandturner updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2413] battery dependency
, improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2399] type alias errors in 
``alias``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2396] sorted the subcommands in help text
jzaefferer added some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2417] crossreferences in command docs
, extended 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2386] ``touch``
 to take multiple args
, fixed some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/58] broken links in the installation instructions
LhKipp updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/125] book with the new time units
ongardie fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/blog/pull/26] unnecessary execute perms in the blog
, fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/blog/pull/25] atom feed on the blog
, fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-book/pull/30] some broken links in the contributor book
rofrol fixed some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/blog/pull/24] typos in the recent blog post
ryuichi1208 updated 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2394] docker file to clear the apt cache
thegedge cleaned up some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2435] unnecessary dependencies in the completer
, made 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2389] lite-parse more forgiving
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2388] completions for short-hand flags
, made 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2387] Nu's completer a bit more standalone
,
vpperego added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-book/pull/29] Portuguese translation of the contributor book
